4. Algorithm

Traverse the string.

If character is '('

Push its index into open stack.

If character is '*'

Push its index into star stack.

If character is ')'

1. If open stack is not empty

Pop open stack.


2. Else if star stack is not empty

Pop star stack.


3. Otherwise

Return false.




---

After traversal,

There may still be unmatched '('.

Match them using '*'.

While both stacks are not empty:

if openIndex < starIndex

Pop both.

Otherwise,

Return false.

Finally,

If open stack is empty,

Return true.

Else,

Return false.


